Implemented the thermal hysteresis controller in:

- `components/controller/controller.c`

Added visible self-verification in:

- `agent_tests/test_controller.py`

What changed:
- Boot initializes `SAFE_OFF` / heater off
- `TEMP < 47` => `HEATING` / heater on
- `TEMP > 52` => `SAFE_OFF` / heater off
- `47..49` => preserves prior actuator state, reports `HOLDING`
- `50..52` rising vs previous valid sample => early heater off, reports `HOLDING`
- `50..52` non-rising => preserves prior actuator state, reports `HOLDING`
- Malformed input => heater off
- Explicit sensor timeout => heater off, `timed_out = true`
- Stale valid sensor data `> 1000 ms` => heater off, `timed_out = true`
- Normal no-new-frame controller steps do not fault before timeout

Visible verification completed:
- `source .embedded_eval_env.sh && python3 tools/run_build.py`
- `source .embedded_eval_env.sh && python3 tools/run_self_tests.py`
- `source .embedded_eval_env.sh && python3 tools/run_eval.py`

Self-tests cover the checklist, including:
- controller-level acceptance tests for each policy bullet
- a visible closed-loop host-side probe staying `<= 56 C`
- firmware-level UART end-to-end probes for nominal warmup, malformed input, and stale-timeout behavior

